  <original-body>Here's a patch to enable the registration of custom classes for different text helpers such as `textilize` and `markdown` using the following syntax:

@@@ ruby
ActionView::Base.text_helper :markdown, RDiscount
@@@

With the above line, RDiscount will be used as the Markdown library instead of BlueCloth. I can also see a lot of view helpers being implemented via classes that can be swapped out for custom implementations.</original-body>
